Player5
\-Oh, it's just you four... you startled me.
Player5
\-It's alright, that's on me for not
being alert. Anyways, how's it been?
Actor4
\p3It's been good... um...
Player5
\-Right, you don't know my name.
Player5
\-Look, you four are heroes and all, but even then,
I can't risk having anyone finding out my name.
Information spreads quickly, and I can't afford
having someone with bad intentions finding out.
Player5
\-With names come a past... a past
that I'm not eager to have dug up.
Actor4
\p2Makes sense... so, why are you here?
Player5
\-Well, I'm sure it's not for the same reason as
you four. I'm only out here to get some loot from
these monsters. Some events over the past few weeks
have pushed me to get some equipment upgrades.
Player5
\-Since you've come this far already, you probably
have some items of interest on you as well. If I
were you, I'd head back to Telluria Castle Town and
make some stronger gear before heading forward.
Player5
\-Though considering how far you've made it on your journey, I'm sure
you can make an informed decision for yourselves. Restock in town and
come back stronger, or keep pushing forward with whatever you have left.
Player5
\-Whatever happens, be warned that just up
ahead is the World Tree. It's a dangerous
maze that not a lot of travelers manage
to find their way out of.
Actor4
\p4Thanks for the advice.
Player5
\-You're welcome, \N[4]. It was good to see
you four, but I'm leaving the forest now.
Good luck in the World Tree.

Lost Forest
RECOMMENDED LEVEL: 13-16
The Lost Forest is a long, winding maze of
twisting tree hallways and natural enemies.
Some say that \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] had no interference
in creating the monsters here, and quite
frankly, that may be correct. Why would he
animate beets of all things?
Regardless, those who find their way through
will be rewarded with entry to the World Tree...
if that's even much of a reward.
Please have proper adventuring gear
before entering!
Going further in unprepared may very well be the
end of you! Proceed with caution!
